The paper discusses the issue of reproducibility in research, which is a concern in many fields including computer science. The decision tree used to classify terminology is a common method in software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions funding agencies and journals, which are relevant to cybernetics (cs.CY) and cryptography (cs.CR) respectively. The use of terminology is also important in programming languages (cs.PL) and databases (cs.DB) where consistency is crucial.
